label: MH-S512
info_overview: Touch Panel Switch is a wall panel built-in with Z-Wave Plus module. With its stylish design and stable performance, the panel can be used to control house-hold electrical appliances like lamp, motor, coffee machine, TV set etc. It supports basic command class，multi channel command class and multi channel association command class, also works as a repeater in a Z-Wave network. This product can be included and operated in any Z-Wave network with other Z-Wave certified devices from any other manufacturers.
info_inclusion:
INCLUDING the device into Z-Wave network:

  • Set controller into INCLUSION mode. Follow instructions provided by controller manufacturer.
  • Press and hold any key on the panel for 8 seconds or 3 clicks in quick succession.

Note: If inclusion is successful, all INDICATION LEDs on the panel will flash 4 times.
info_exclusion:
EXCLUDING the device from Z-Wave network:

  • Set controller into EXCLUSION mode. Follow instructions provided by controller manufacturer.
  • Press and hold any key on the panel for 8 seconds or 3 clicks in quick succession.

Note: If the exclusion is successful, all INDICATION LEDs on the panel will flash 4 times. The exclusion will delete all association data.

category_description: Any device attached to the wall that controls a binary status of something, for ex. a light switch

parameters.label: State saved after pwr failure
parameters.overview: 0: not saved, switch will be off when powered again 1: saved, switch will keep the same state when powered again

parameters.label: Scene Respond
parameters.overview: 0: All switches respond Scene CC 1: only S1 responds

parameters.label: ALL ON/ALL OFF
parameters.overview:
0: forbid ALL ON, forbid ALL OFF
1: forbid ALL ON, allow ALL OFF
2: allow ALL ON, forbid ALL OFF
255: allow ALL ON, allow ALL OFF

commandclass.name: NO_OPERATION
commandclass.label: No Operation - used for PINGing a device.
